78.7	Sarah_McLachlan	Sarah McLachlan	Sarah Ann McLachlan, OC, OBC (born January 28, 1968)) is a Canadian musician, singer and songwriter. Known for her emotional ballads and mezzo-soprano vocal range, as of 2009, she has sold over 40 million albums worldwide. McLachlan's best-selling album to date is Surfacing, for which she won two Grammy Awards (out of four nominations) and four Juno Awards. In addition to her personal artistic efforts, she founded the Lilith Fair tour, which showcased female musicians. The Lilith Fair concert tours took place from 1997 to 1999, and resumed in the summer of 2010. Since 2006 she has also been known as a highly visible supporter of the ASPCA, as well as various other charities.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/82/Sarah_McLachlan_29_July_2010.jpg/220px-Sarah_McLachlan_29_July_2010.jpg
